# Normalize line endings to LF in the working tree on every platform.
#
# Without this, GitHub-hosted Windows runners' Git installations default to
# `core.autocrlf=true`, which converts checked-out files to CRLF. The
# `crate_universe` Bazel module extension records SHA-256 hashes of
# `Cargo.toml`, `Cargo.lock`, and 17 per-crate `Cargo.toml` files in
# `MODULE.bazel.lock`'s `recordedFileInputs`. CRLF bytes change the SHA, the
# lockfile check fails, and Bazel re-runs `cargo-bazel.exe splice` (~50 s) on
# every Windows test invocation — see the diagnostic data captured in PR #185.
* text=auto eol=lf

# OpenNGC catalog data is imported verbatim from the upstream openNGC source
# (https://github.com/mattiaverga/OpenNGC) and uses CRLF. Preserve byte-for-byte
# so the import script's expectations stay valid and so a re-import is a clean
# diff against upstream.
crates/rp-catalog/src/data/*.csv -text

# FITS fixtures are binary; be explicit so Git never tries text conversion on
# them.
*.fits -text
